<p>Below is a quick cheat sheet for getting up and running with <a href="https://www.portainer.io/">Portainer</a>, generally I make use of <a href="https://unraid.net/">Unraid</a> for running my <a href="https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop/">Docker</a> containers however when it comes to running <a href="https://github.com/zwave-js">Z-Wave JS</a> I needed to run it on another computer that had a free USB port :)</p>
<h2 id="starting-the-container">Starting the container</h2>
{% highlight "shell" %}
sudo docker run -d -p 8000:8000 -p 9443:9443 --force-create --name portainer --restart=always -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock -v portainer_data:/data portainer/portainer-ce
{% endhighlight %}

<h2 id="stopping-the-container">Stopping the container</h2>
{% highlight "shell" %}
sudo docker container stop portainer
{% endhighlight %}

<h2 id="removing-the-container">Removing the container</h2>
{% highlight "shell" %}
sudo docker container rm portainer
{% endhighlight %}

